SCNN-pytorch/blob/master/train.py#L90\r\n        if torch.cuda.device_count() > 1:\r\n            self.model = torch.nn.DataParallel(self.model, device_ids=[0, 1, 2])\r\n        self.model.to(args.device)\r\n```\r\n\r\n# Possible solution\r\nThe following code change will make it work for machines with 2, 4, .. GPUs.\r\n\r\n```python\r\n        if torch.cuda.device_count() > 1:\r\n            device_ids = list(range(torch.cuda.device_count()))\r\n            self.model = torch.nn.DataParallel(self.model, device_ids=device_ids)\r\n        self.model.to(args.device)\r\n```","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Tramac/Fast-SCNN-pytorch/issues/10/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Tramac/Fast-SCNN-pytorch/issues/10/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}